{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://leoshcn.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Halloween Martin (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Halloween_Martin\" title=\"Halloween Martin\">Halloween Martin</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> became one of the first modern DJs at a time when radio widely discriminated against women?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halloween_Martin","retrieved":1772949716682},{"title":"a dictionary of women's quotations (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the editors of <b><a href=\"/wiki/Violets_and_Vinegar\" title=\"Violets and Vinegar\">a dictionary of women's quotations</a></b> were motivated to create it when they observed that mixed-gender volumes were 90% men?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Violets_and_Vinegar","retrieved":1772949716684},{"title":"Ruth Wagner (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Ruth_Wagner\" title=\"Ruth Wagner\">Ruth Wagner</a></b>, the minister of culture in Hesse from 1999 to 2003, was nicknamed <a href=\"/wiki/Mother_Courage_(character)\" title=\"Mother Courage (character)\">Mother Courage</a> of Hesse?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruth_Wagner","retrieved":1772949716691},{"title":"an Irish-language parody of Mean Girls (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that there is <b><a href=\"/wiki/Cail%C3%ADn%C3%AD_Gr%C3%A1nna\" title=\"Cailíní Gránna\">an Irish-language parody of <i>Mean Girls</i></a></b><span style=\"padding-left:0.15em;\">?</span>","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cail%C3%ADn%C3%AD_Gr%C3%A1nna","retrieved":1772949716691},{"title":"Carla Williams (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Carla_Williams_(photographer)\" title=\"Carla Williams (photographer)\">Carla Williams</a></b> got into self-portraits in part due to the poor representation of Black women in her photography history class?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carla_Williams_(photographer)","